		<title>08ARTS AND CRAFTS</title>
		<content>  There is a craft potter working in   
 the village; the potter and his family
 run courses in pottery, spinning and  
 weaving.                              
  Twice a year there is a flea         
 market in the village hall at which   
 local produce and craft work is sold. 
 Each person with something to sell    
 hires a stall. One of these markets is
 usually held to co-incide with the    
 Severn Bore.                          
  There is a small craft shop selling  
 rustic trellis, arches, garden        
 furniture and gnomes.                 
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
